                    <h1 class="title" id="page-title">
          Privacy and Cookie Policy        </h1>
                          <div class="tabs">
                  </div>
                          <div class="region region-content">
    <div id="block-system-main" class="block block-system">

    
  <div class="content">
    <article id="node-19637" class="node node-page node-full clearfix" role="article">

      
  
  <div class="content clearfix">
    <div class="field field-name-field-social-page field-type-social-buttons field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><div class="social-buttons"><span class="social-button"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/" onclick="windowpop('https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=', 500, 500); return false;" style="padding-right:10px;"><img src="http://cdn.portableapps.com/btnShareFacebook57x20v2.png" width="57" height="20" alt="Share on Facebook" title="Share on Facebook"></a></span><span class="social-button"><a href="https://twitter.com/" onclick="windowpop('https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=' + document.title.replace(' | PortableApps.com - Portable software for USB, portable and cloud drives','').replace('&','%26') + '&via=PortableApps&url=', 500, 500);return false;" style="padding-right:10px;"><img src="http://cdn.portableapps.com/btnTweet57x20v2.png" width="57" height="20" alt="Tweet" title="Share on Twitter"></a></span><span class="social-button"><a href="https://plus.google.com/" onclick="windowpop('https://plus.google.com/share?url=', 500, 500); return false;" style="padding-right:10px;"><img src="http://cdn.portableapps.com/btnShareGooglePlus57x20v2.png" width="57" height="20" alt="Share on Google+" title="Share on Google+"></a></span><span class="social-button"><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/" onclick="windowpop('https://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?url=', 500, 500); return false;" style="padding-right:10px;"><img src="http://cdn.portableapps.com/btnShareLinkedIn57x20v2.png" width="57" height="20" alt="Share on LinkedIn" title="Share on LinkedIn"></a><script type='text/javascript'>
function windowpop(url, width, height) {
    var leftPosition, topPosition;
    //Allow for borders.
    leftPosition = (window.screen.width / 2) - ((width / 2) + 10);
    //Allow for title and status bars.
    topPosition = (window.screen.height / 2) - ((height / 2) + 50);
    //Open the window.
    window.open(url+document.URL, "Window2", "status=no,height=" + height + ",width=" + width + ",resizable=yes,left=" + leftPosition + ",top=" + topPosition + ",screenX=" + leftPosition + ",screenY=" + topPosition + ",toolbar=no,menubar=no,scrollbars=no,location=no,directories=no");
}</script><div></div></span></div></div></div></div><div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p><img width="128" height="128" align="right" alt="" src="http://cdn.portableapps.com/_icon_-_privacy_oxygen_128.png" />This is the web site of PortableApps.com. We can be reached via email or by telephone on our <a href="http://portableapps.com/about/contact">contact page</a>.  We are located in New York, NY in the United States of America.  We think your privacy is important, so we have posted this privacy policy to explain the information we collect, how it is used, how we protect it and how you can change it.</p>

<img width="140" align="left" alt="" src="http://cdn.portableapps.com/_icon_-_privacy1.png" alt="Your data is used only for the intended use." />
<img width="140" align="left" alt="" src="http://cdn.portableapps.com/_icon_-_privacy2.png" alt="Your data is never bartered or sold." />
<img width="140" align="left" alt="" src="http://cdn.portableapps.com/_icon_-_privacy3.png" alt="Your data is never given to advertisers." />
<img width="140" align="left" alt="" src="http://cdn.portableapps.com/_icon_-_privacy4.png" alt="Data is given to law enforcement only when legal process is followed." />

<h2>Information Collected</h2>

<p>For each visitor to our Web page, our Web server automatically recognizes IP addresses.</p>

<p>We collect the email addresses of those who post messages to our forums or otherwise register for an account or our email newsletter.</p>

<p>We use cookies to store visitors preferences and allow registered users to log in.</p>

<h2>Cookies</h2>

<p>Like nearly all websites worldwide, PortableApps.com uses cookies when you visit our site.  Cookies originating from portableapps.com are used to allow logins to the site and keep track of your preferences and selections while you use our site (like whether you've expanded or collapsed certain forum views).  These cookies are strictly necessary for these specific functions and you will be unable to login or keep track of preferences without them.  Cookies originating from our content delivery network (cdn.portableapps.com) are used to keep track of when you last loaded images and other assets in your browser.  These cookies are optional, but you may wind up re-downloading certain images on subsequent visits to our site.  Cookies originating from additional domains (google, adsense, etc) are used to display advertising and handle analytics for visiting the site.  These cookies are optional and blocking them will not affect your visit, but may result in us not being able to track you as a visitor which can affect donation/sponsorship funding.  PortableApps.com has specifically chosen not to use dynamic social media buttons to protect your privacy, so no cookies will be added for social networks.</p>

<h2>Unsubscribing</h2>

<p>If you have subscribed to our email newsletter and no longer want to receive email from us, you can unsubscribe directly via the link at the bottom of the newsletter or by visiting the <a href="http://portableapps.com/newsletter">newsletter page</a>.</p>

<h2>Information Sharing</h2>

<p>We do not share, sell or otherwise give away your personal information such as your email address to 3rd parties.</p>

<p>The information we collect is disclosed when legally required to do so, at the request of governmental authorities conducting an investigation, to verify or enforce compliance with the policies governing our Website and applicable laws or to protect against misuse or unauthorized use of our Website.</p>

<p>We have a relationship with Google to place ads on our Web pages. As a result of your visit to our site, Google may collect information such as your domain type, your IP address and clickstream information. For further information, consult the <a href="http://www.google.com/privacy.html">Google Privacy Center</a>.  We do not share any information you provide us with Google or other advertisers.</p>

<h2>Policy Changes</h2>

<p>From time to time, we may use customer information for new, unanticipated uses not previously disclosed in our privacy notice. If our information practices change at some time in the future we will post the policy changes to our Web site to notify you of these changes and provide you with the ability to opt out of these new uses. If you are concerned about how your information is used, you should check back at our Web site periodically.</p>

<h2>Your Information</h2>

<p>Upon request we provide site visitors with access to unique identifier information (e.g., customer number or password) that we maintain about them, communications that the visitor has directed to our site (e.g., emails, customer inquiries).  Visitors can access this information by visiting <a href="http://portableapps.com/user">their account page</a>.</p>

<p>Upon request we offer visitors the ability to have inaccuracies corrected in contact information, communications that the visitor has directed to the site.  Visitors can have this information corrected by visiting <a href="http://portableapps.com/user">their account page</a>.</p>

<h2>Security</h2>

<p>We have appropriate security measures in place in our physical facilities to protect against the loss, misuse or alteration of information that we have collected from you at our site.  These measures include keycard protocols, biometric scanning protocols and round-the-clock interior and exterior surveillance monitor access to every one of our data centers.  Only authorized data center personnel are granted access credentials to our data centers. No one else can enter the production area of the datacenter without prior clearance and an appropriate escort. Every data center employee undergoes multiple and thorough background security checks before they're hired.</p>

<h2>Corrections</h2>

<p>If you feel that this site is not following its stated information policy, you may contact us by email or by telephone on our <a href="http://portableapps.com/about/contact">contact page</a>.</p>

<p><em>This policy was last updated on 2015-07-29</em></p></div></div></div>  </div>

  
  
</article>
